<subSubSection id="C30F91A8FFF6FF88FF74FC59FDBBA41E" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BAAC223FFF6FF88FF74FC59FDBBA41E" blockId="6.[151,1437,151,1076]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<emphasis id="B9611E31FFF6FF88FF74FC59FEE1A43A" bold="true" box="[201,336,1016,1040]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific name is derived from the Latin word 
<emphasis id="B9611E31FFF6FF88FC2FFC59FC7BA43A" box="[914,970,1016,1040]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">brevi</emphasis>
s = short, in reference to the distinctively short uncus in the male genitalia.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
